the burned scraps of the whale, a potent lye is readily made; and whenever any 
adhesiveness from the back of the whale remains clinging to the side, that lye 
quickly exterminates it. Hands go diligently along the bulwarks, and with 
buckets of water and rags restore them to their full tidiness. The soot is 
